Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping the greens and whites separate. Roughly chop the @cilantro{¼%ounce}(roughly chopped). Peel, then thinly slice the @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) into rings. Roughly chop the @pineapple{4%ounce}(roughly chopped) into small pieces, reserving any juice. Slice or tear the @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce}(sliced or torn into small pieces) into small pieces.

Using your hands, stretch out the @pizza dough{10%ounce} into a rough 1/4-inch thick rectangle (about 9"x13"). Place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and prick all over with a #fork{}. Place in the oven for ~{7-10%minutes}, until the dough is just beginning to brown on the edges.

> If you have a rolling pin or wine bottle, we recommend rolling out the dough onto a lightly floured surface.

While the pizza dough cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over high heat. Add the pineapple to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{3-4%minutes} until slightly browned. Add the shallots and the scallion whites to the pan and cook for an additional ~{2%minutes}. When the pizza dough is ready, remove it from the oven and preheat the broiler to high or the oven to 500 degrees.

Top the par-baked pizza dough with the mozzarella cheese, pineapple, shallot, and scallion whites. Tear the @prosciutto{4%ounce}(torn into pieces) into pieces and lay them over the pizza. Return the pizza to the oven for ~{3-5%minutes} more, until the crust is crisp and slightly charred, and the cheese is melted and starting to brown.

== Spiced Honey ==

Make the spiced honey: Add the scallion greens, reserved pineapple juice, @honey{1%tablespoon}, @water{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste) to the same pan you used for the pineapple. Bring to a simmer and cook for about ~{1%minute}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Plate and serve: Cut the Hawaiian pizza into slices and drizzle with the spiced honey. Top with the chopped cilantro and enjoy!